metadata.symbol: Art from Paraguay to the world.
metadata.description: The work is a representation that mixes the myths and legends of Paraguay with part of the universal mythology. In the scene, the Jasyjatere and the Pombero are observed next to goblins, ogres, undead and other specters, observing attentively a fairy, who reads one of the sources of its origin: the book.
